  <title>GLib.Cond.prototype.init</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function init(): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_cond_init()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Initialises a <link xref="GLib.Cond"/> so that it can be used.</p>  <p>This function is useful to initialise a <link xref="GLib.Cond"/> that has been
allocated as part of a larger structure.  It is not necessary to
initialise a <link xref="GLib.Cond"/> that has been statically allocated.</p>  <p>To undo the effect of <link xref="GLib.Cond.init"/> when a <link xref="GLib.Cond"/> is no longer
needed, use <link xref="GLib.Cond.clear"/>.</p>  <p>Calling <link xref="GLib.Cond.init"/> on an already-initialised <link xref="GLib.Cond"/> leads
to undefined behaviour.</p>
  <p>Since 2.32</p>

